this may not be relevant on Android depending on how the graphql variables are generated from the model instance, but on iOS, for scenario 2 and 4, we would generate the graphQL variables based on the model instance. Since the model instance contains the owner field, graphql variables would contain "owner: null", and the requests would fail
Model instance created like let model = Model(id = "111", owner = nil) would generate a graphql variables like
{
   "input": {
      "id": "111",
      "owner": null
   }
}

So, we actually filter the owner out

